Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Algeria. The Algerian authorities have introduced measures to limit the spread of the virus.
Entry and borders
All international flights to and from Algeria have been suspended. All land borders have been closed.
All ferry services have been suspended.
For information on how to return to the UK from Algeria, see Return to the UK
Local measures
Schools, nurseries, universities and mosques have closed, sporting events have been cancelled and many public amenities and public spaces have been shut to the general public.
Further information
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
You can find more information about cases in Algeria on the TravelHealthPro country page.
